ksdk:manifest.name: SDK version 2.2.2 package for MKW36A512xxx4 device
ksdk:manifest.brief: This is SDK version 2.2.2 manifest file. It describes the content of the SDK version 2.2.2 package for MKW36A512xxx4 device and additional settings for tools that support SDK version 2.2.2

board.name: FRDM-KW36
board.description: FRDM-KW36: NXP Freedom Development Platform for Kinetis KW36/35 MCUs

specific.content: The FRDM-KW36 is a development platform enabled by the Kinetis W series KW36/35 family built on ARM Cortex-M0+ processor with integrated 2.4 GHz transceiver supporting Bluetooth Smart/Bluetooth Low Energy (BLE) v4.2, Generic FSK. The FRDM-KW36 is form-factor compatible with the Arduino R3 pin layout for more expansion options.

device.name: MKW35Z4
device.description: KW35Z: Kinetis KW35Z - 2.4 GHz BLE and Generic FSK connectivity Wireless Radio Microcontroller (MCU) based on ARM Cortex-M0+ Core

specific.content: The KW35Z devices, which include both Automotive and Industrial devices, are highly integrated single-chip devices that enable Bluetooth low energy (BLE) and Generic FSK connectivity for automotive and industrial embedded systems. The applications center on bridging the embedded world with smartphones to enhance the human interface experience, share embedded data with the cloud, or enable wireless firmware updates. The KW35Z MCU integrates a 2.4 GHz transceiv operating in the 2.36GHz to 2.48GHz range supporting a range of Generic FSK, an ARM Cortex-M0+ CPU, up to 512 KB Flash and up to 64 KB SRAM, BLE Link Layer hardware and Generic FSK Link layer controller hardware and peripherals optimized to meet the requirements of the target applications. The BLE transceiver supports up to 8 concurrent connections in any master-slave combination.

device.name: MKW36A4
device.description: KW36A: Kinetis KW36A - 2.4 GHz BLE and Generic FSK connectivity Wireless Radio Microcontroller (MCU) based on ARM Cortex-M0+ Core, with FlexCAN and FlexNVM memory, Automotive qualification.

specific.content: The KW36A Automotive devices, are highly integrated single-chip devices that enable Bluetooth low energy (BLE) and Generic FSK connectivity for automotive embedded systems. The applications center on bridging the embedded world with smartphones to enhance the human interface experience, share embedded data with the cloud, or enable wireless firmware updates. The KW36A MCU integrates a 2.4 GHz transceiv operating in the 2.36GHz to 2.48GHz range supporting a range of Generic FSK, an ARM Cortex-M0+ CPU, up to 256 KB Flash, up to 256 KB FlexNVM and up to 64 KB SRAM, BLE Link Layer hardware and Generic FSK Link layer controller hardware and peripherals optimized to meet the requirements of the target applications. The BLE transceiver supports up to 8 concurrent connections in any master-slave combination.
